1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:02,715
One day a student spoke to me very honestly.

2
00:00:02,715 --> 00:00:04,849
He looked tired and a little sad.

3
00:00:04,849 --> 00:00:09,660
He said, teacher, everyday I sit on my chair with my English book.

4
00:00:09,660 --> 00:00:11,120
I really want to study.

5
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:13,879
I even promise myself I will not waste time.

6
00:00:13,935 --> 00:00:16,274
I open the book and read one line.

7
00:00:16,274 --> 00:00:20,355
Then I say to myself, I will check my phone for just one minute.

8
00:00:20,355 --> 00:00:21,654
Only one minute.

9
00:00:21,654 --> 00:00:25,815
But when I look again, one full hour is already gone

10
00:00:25,815 --> 00:00:28,175
and my book is still open on the same page.

11
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:33,810
Maybe you smiled when you heard this because maybe this story is also your story.

12
00:00:33,810 --> 00:00:35,850
You don't want to waste time.

13
00:00:35,850 --> 00:00:40,370
You want to learn English but somehow your finger opens TikTok,

14
00:00:40,370 --> 00:00:44,905
Instagram or YouTube by itself And after that, you feel bad.

15
00:00:44,905 --> 00:00:47,525
You say, tomorrow I will study properly.

16
00:00:47,525 --> 00:00:51,005
But tomorrow comes and the same thing happens again.

17
00:00:51,005 --> 00:00:53,805
Let me tell you something important as your teacher.

18
00:00:53,805 --> 00:00:55,105
You are not lazy.

19
00:00:55,250 --> 00:00:56,790
You are not weak.

20
00:00:56,790 --> 00:00:58,250
You are just human.

21
00:00:58,250 --> 00:01:00,390
Let me explain this in a very simple way.

22
00:01:00,390 --> 00:01:04,390
Inside your brain, there is something called a happy chemical.

23
00:01:04,390 --> 00:01:10,609
When you watch short videos, laugh, or see something interesting, your brain feels happy very fast.

24
00:01:10,785 --> 00:01:12,908
It says, oh, I like this. Give me more.

25
00:01:13,185 --> 00:01:14,904
Scrolling feels easy.

26
00:01:14,904 --> 00:01:16,085
Fast happiness.

27
00:01:16,085 --> 00:01:17,064
No thinking.

28
00:01:17,064 --> 00:01:18,005
No effort.

29
00:01:18,005 --> 00:01:20,225
But learning English feels different.

30
00:01:20,145 --> 00:01:21,465
You open a book.

31
00:01:21,465 --> 00:01:22,865
You see many new words.

32
00:01:22,830 --> 00:01:24,850
Your brain feels tired.

33
00:01:24,850 --> 00:01:26,469
It says, this is hard.

34
00:01:26,469 --> 00:01:28,370
Let's do something easy instead.

35
00:01:28,370 --> 00:01:30,150
So your brain is not bad.

36
00:01:30,150 --> 00:01:32,150
It is just used to fast fun.

37
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:35,405
The good news is this, we can train your brain again

38
00:01:35,405 --> 00:01:40,125
and I will show you how step by step like a teacher helping a student.

39
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:42,225
First, we need to slow your mind.

40
00:01:42,225 --> 00:01:44,884
I am not telling you to throw away your phone.

41
00:01:44,884 --> 00:01:45,345
No.

42
00:01:45,345 --> 00:01:46,685
That is not real life.

43
00:01:46,685 --> 00:01:48,825
I want you to try something very small.

44
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:52,669
Everyday, give your brain just ten minutes of quiet time.

45
00:01:52,669 --> 00:01:55,689
No phone, no music, no messages.

46
00:01:55,689 --> 00:02:00,350
You can walk slowly, you can sit near a window, you can look at the sky.

47
00:02:00,350 --> 00:02:05,434
At first, it will feel boring, very boring, like waiting for the internet to load.

48
00:02:05,434 --> 00:02:08,674
But after a few days, something interesting happens.

49
00:02:08,595 --> 00:02:10,235
Your mind becomes calm.

50
00:02:10,235 --> 00:02:13,755
Small things start to feel nice again, a quiet moment.

51
00:02:13,755 --> 00:02:16,915
One new English word, your brain slowly learns.

52
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:18,930
Hey, this feels good too.

53
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:21,510
Now, let's talk about making English fun again.

54
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:24,429
Many students see English like a big monster.

55
00:02:24,350 --> 00:02:25,269
Scary.

56
00:02:25,269 --> 00:02:26,470
Too many words.

57
00:02:26,470 --> 00:02:28,290
But English is not a monster.

58
00:02:28,290 --> 00:02:29,290
It is a journey.

59
00:02:29,290 --> 00:02:31,715
Think of learning English like traveling.

60
00:02:31,715 --> 00:02:34,255
Every new word is a small place you visit.

61
00:02:34,255 --> 00:02:36,535
Every sentence is one step forward.

62
00:02:36,535 --> 00:02:39,175
When you learn a word, don't just read it.

63
00:02:39,175 --> 00:02:40,275
Imagine it.

64
00:02:40,275 --> 00:02:46,019
If the word is journey, think about your own life, your struggles, your dreams.

65
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:48,120
You are not just learning English.

66
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:51,260
You are learning to see the world in a new way.

67
00:02:51,260 --> 00:02:53,859
You can make English part of your daily life.

68
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:56,320
Watch short English videos you enjoy.

69
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:58,980
Listen to English songs and try to sing slowly.

70
00:02:59,265 --> 00:03:02,464
Write one simple English sentence under your photo.

71
00:03:02,385 --> 00:03:03,545
No pressure.

72
00:03:03,545 --> 00:03:04,425
No fear.

73
00:03:04,425 --> 00:03:07,064
Learning should feel natural, not painful.

74
00:03:07,064 --> 00:03:09,125
Now, me share a powerful secret.

75
00:03:09,125 --> 00:03:10,885
Your brain loves rewards.

76
00:03:10,885 --> 00:03:12,945
So we use rewards in a smart way.

77
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:15,600
Study for twenty minutes, then stop.

78
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:16,980
Take a short break.

79
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:18,019
Drink water.

80
00:03:18,019 --> 00:03:19,220
Stretch your body.

81
00:03:19,220 --> 00:03:20,900
Check your phone for a few minutes.

82
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:23,060
After studying, mark your progress.

83
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:25,200
A tick mark, a small star.

84
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,099
It feels good.

85
00:03:26,099 --> 00:03:26,359
Right?

86
00:03:26,359 --> 00:03:28,855
Like saying, yes, I did something today.

87
00:03:28,855 --> 00:03:31,015
Small wins build strong habits.

88
00:03:31,015 --> 00:03:33,194
Now, one more important thing.

89
00:03:33,194 --> 00:03:35,735
Learn English with curiosity, not fear.

90
00:03:35,735 --> 00:03:37,835
Don't learn English only for exams.

91
00:03:37,835 --> 00:03:39,255
Learn it for your life.

92
00:03:39,255 --> 00:03:42,015
If you love games, watch gaming videos in English.

93
00:03:42,015 --> 00:03:46,240
If you love short videos, follow English creators who speak slowly.

94
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:50,680
When English connects with what you already love, your brain does not fight.

95
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:54,240
Your brain follows because English is not a punishment.

96
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:58,615
It is a door, And every word you learn opens that door a little more.

97
00:03:58,615 --> 00:04:00,075
Now listen carefully.

98
00:04:00,075 --> 00:04:01,775
Your brain is not broken.

99
00:04:01,775 --> 00:04:04,115
It just got used to fast rewards.

100
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:06,074
Now you are teaching us something better.

101
00:04:06,074 --> 00:04:07,275
Real progress.

102
00:04:07,275 --> 00:04:08,594
Start very small.

103
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:10,200
Five minutes today.

104
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:11,579
Ten minutes tomorrow.

105
00:04:11,579 --> 00:04:14,400
One day, you will not force yourself to study.

106
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,660
You will want to.

107
00:04:15,660 --> 00:04:17,440
And now imagine this future.

108
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:21,632
One day, sooner than you think, you will watch a movie in English

109
00:04:21,731 --> 00:04:24,225
and understand it without subtitles.

110
00:04:24,225 --> 00:04:26,685
One day, you will speak English without fear.

111
00:04:26,685 --> 00:04:32,805
You will make new friends, travel, get better opportunities, maybe even get the job you dream about.

112
00:04:32,805 --> 00:04:37,145
And all of this will happen because today, you chose learning over scrolling.

113
00:04:37,229 --> 00:04:39,350
You chose growth over escape.

114
00:04:39,350 --> 00:04:42,290
That is how you become addicted to learning English.

115
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:45,510
Not addicted to your phone, but addicted to progress.

116
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:49,590
And trust me as your teacher, your future self will thank you for this choice.
